Bonds ‘Chose Not to Tell Truth,’ Prosecutor Says in Closing Arguments

-- B y   K a r e n   G u l l o
-- 
2011-04-07T16:53:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/bonds-chose-not-to-tell-truth-prosecutor-says-in-closing-arguements.html
Former  San Francisco  Giants
outfielder  Barry Bonds , who holds baseball’s record for home
runs, “chose not to tell the truth” and testified falsely
before a federal grand jury when he said he didn’t knowingly
take steroids provided by his trainer, Assistant U.S. Attorney
Jeff Nedrow told a jury in closing arguments today in San
Francisco.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Gullo in San Francisco at 
 kgullo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Andrew Dunn  at 
 adunn8@bloomberg.net  